<H2>Game Mode Dialog</H2> 
The game mode dialog looks like this:<P>

<IMG SRC="game_mode.jpg" ALT="Map Properties Dialog" VSPACE="" ALIGN="LEFT" BORDER="0" > <br clear=all>

<P>
This dialog is used to set and change the game modes supported by the current map open. The validate map button will scan you map and add a check mark next to the game modes that could be supported. Every game mode has different requirements. Once the game modes selected are the ones you want click ok to save the game modes to the map or cancle to back out.<P>

The requirements for the different game modes are listed below:
<UL>
<LI> <B>Deathmatch</B>, At least <B>one</B> spawn point.
<LI> <B>Team Deathmatch</B>, At least <B>one</B> red spawn area, and at least <B>one</B> blue spawn area.
<LI> <B>Capture the Flag</B>, At least <B>one</B> red spawn area, at least <B>one</B> blue spawn area, at least <B>one</B> red flag, and at least <B>one</B> blue flag.
<LI> <B>King of the Hill</B>, At least <B>one</B> spawn point, and at least <B>one</B> king of the hill area.
</UL>
